<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="floor" id="floor">floor</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Sintaxe:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">floor</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

A função floor() devolve o maior inteiro não maior que arg. Por exemplo,
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     y <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="nu16">6.04</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     x <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="kw3">floor</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> y <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

alteraria x para 6.0, e

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     y <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="sy2">-</span><span class="nu16">6.04</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     x <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="kw3">floor</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> y <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

alteraria x para -7.0.
</p>

<p>
O C++ também fornece as seguintes formas sobre-carregadas (overload):

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">floor</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a floorf() em C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">floor</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a floorl() em C99</span></pre>
<p>
Tópicos Relacionados: <a href="ceil" class="wikilink1" title="br-pt:numeric:c:ceil">ceil</a>, <a href="fmod" class="wikilink1" title="br-pt:numeric:c:fmod">fmod</a>

</p>

